Security alert was sounded in Pathankot early today when two suspicious bags were found lying unattended just a few yards away from the military base. The area was cordoned off.The police recovered mobile tower batteries from the bags. Security has been beefed up in the area and a search operation is underway to find the owner of the bags. On Tuesday, an abandoned Scorpio SUV was found in Gurdaspur district. Punjab: Unidentified bag recovered near Mamun army cantonment in Pathankot, police found 2 mobile tower batteries from the bag after search pic.twitter.com/lT5bWouu3zThe SUV reportedly broke a police barrier before it was stopped.